<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-10-03T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-10-03T04:00:00-05:00" n="478" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d478">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.512/686: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Cunningham</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-10-03T17:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">October 3,
                                        1927—5 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received October 3—7:13
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Referring to Department’s October 1, 6 p.m., I am preparing to undertake
                            to carry out recommendations contained in paragraph 2 [<hi rend="italic">7</hi>] of my September 26, 4 p.m. and am so informing American
                            warehousemen as well as importers in American ships. Full report by
                            mail. Repeated to the Legation.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Cunningham</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>